    <h2 id="section-horizon">On the Horizon</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Your current usage shows mostly configuration exploration—the real frontier is unleashing Claude Code on autonomous, multi-step engineering workflows that compound value across an entire codebase.</p>
    <div class="horizon-section">
      
        <div class="horizon-card">
          <div class="horizon-title">Autonomous Test-Driven Feature Development</div>
          <div class="horizon-possible">Instead of single edits, Claude can autonomously implement entire features by writing failing tests first, then iterating implementations until all tests pass—running in a tight loop without your intervention. Combined with subagents reviewing each iteration, you get production-ready code with verified behavior in one session.</div>
          <div class="horizon-tip"><strong>Getting started:</strong> Use the Task tool to spawn a coding subagent paired with a test-runner subagent, and let Claude Code drive the red-green-refactor cycle via Bash until tests pass.</div>
          <div class="pattern-prompt"><div class="prompt-label">Paste into Claude Code:</div><code>I want you to implement [FEATURE] using strict TDD. Spawn a subagent to: (1) write comprehensive failing tests covering edge cases, (2) implement minimal code to pass them, (3) run the test suite via Bash, (4) iterate on failures autonomously up to 10 times, (5) refactor for clarity once green. After completion, spawn a second reviewer subagent to critique the implementation for security, performance, and maintainability, then apply its recommendations. Don&apos;t ask me for confirmation between steps—just report the final diff.</code><button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyText(this)">Copy</button></div>
        </div>
      
        <div class="horizon-card">
          <div class="horizon-title">Parallel Multi-Agent Codebase Audit</div>
          <div class="horizon-possible">Launch multiple Claude agents simultaneously, each owning a different audit dimension—security, performance, dead code, dependency drift, test coverage gaps—then synthesize their findings into a prioritized backlog. What used to be a week of senior-engineer review collapses into a single coffee break.</div>
          <div class="horizon-tip"><strong>Getting started:</strong> Use the Task tool to dispatch parallel general-purpose subagents with distinct audit charters, then have the orchestrator merge results into a ranked Markdown report.</div>
          <div class="pattern-prompt"><div class="prompt-label">Paste into Claude Code:</div><code>Audit this entire codebase in parallel. Spawn 5 subagents simultaneously with these charters: (1) security vulnerabilities and unsafe patterns, (2) performance hotspots and N+1 issues, (3) dead/unreachable code and unused dependencies, (4) test coverage gaps with concrete missing cases, (5) documentation drift versus actual behavior. Each subagent returns a structured JSON list of findings with file:line, severity, and a suggested fix. Merge all findings into AUDIT.md ranked by impact-to-effort ratio, and auto-create a fix branch with the top 3 trivial fixes already applied.</code><button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyText(this)">Copy</button></div>
        </div>
      
        <div class="horizon-card">
          <div class="horizon-title">Self-Bootstrapping Project Onboarding</div>
          <div class="horizon-possible">Rather than running /init on empty directories, point Claude at any unfamiliar repo and have it autonomously map architecture, infer conventions, run the build, fix what&apos;s broken, and produce a complete CLAUDE.md plus an interactive onboarding doc—turning context-gathering from hours into minutes.</div>
          <div class="horizon-tip"><strong>Getting started:</strong> Combine Read, Glob, and Bash with a planning subagent to explore systematically, then generate living documentation that future Claude sessions can leverage.</div>
          <div class="pattern-prompt"><div class="prompt-label">Paste into Claude Code:</div><code>Onboard yourself to this codebase autonomously. Steps: (1) map the directory structure and identify the language/framework/build system, (2) run the install and build commands, fixing any breakage you encounter, (3) run the test suite and document which tests pass/fail, (4) trace the main entry point and produce an architecture diagram in Mermaid, (5) infer code conventions from the top 20 files, (6) write a comprehensive CLAUDE.md with project overview, key commands, conventions, gotchas, and a &apos;common tasks&apos; cookbook. Also create ONBOARDING.md aimed at a new human engineer. Work without asking me questions—make reasonable assumptions and note them.</code><button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyText(this)">Copy</button></div>
        </div>
      
    </div>
    

    
    <div class="fun-ending">
      <div class="fun-headline">"User asked Claude to /init an empty folder, expecting magic"</div>
      <div class="fun-detail">In one session, the user ran /init to generate a CLAUDE.md file, but the working directory was completely empty. Claude had to politely report there was nothing to analyze before the user exited.</div>
    </div>
    

    
  </div>
  <script>
    function toggleCollapsible(header) {
      header.classList.toggle('open');
      const content = header.nextElementSibling;
      content.classList.toggle('open');
    }
    function copyText(btn) {
      const code = btn.previousElementSibling;
      navigator.clipboard.writeText(code.textContent).then(() => {
        btn.textContent = 'Copied!';
        setTimeout(() => { btn.textContent = 'Copy'; }, 2000);
      });
    }
    function copyCmdItem(idx) {
      const checkbox = document.getElementById('cmd-' + idx);
      if (checkbox) {
        const text = checkbox.dataset.text;
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
          const btn = checkbox.nextElementSibling.querySelector('.copy-btn');
          if (btn) { btn.textContent = 'Copied!'; setTimeout(() => { btn.textContent = 'Copy'; }, 2000); }
        });
      }
    }
    function copyAllCheckedClaudeMd() {
      const checkboxes = document.querySelectorAll('.cmd-checkbox:checked');
      const texts = [];
      checkboxes.forEach(cb => {
        if (cb.dataset.text) { texts.push(cb.dataset.text); }
      });
      const combined = texts.join('\n');
      const btn = document.querySelector('.copy-all-btn');
      if (btn) {
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(combined).then(() => {
          btn.textContent = 'Copied ' + texts.length + ' items!';
          btn.classList.add('copied');
          setTimeout(() => { btn.textContent = 'Copy All Checked'; btn.classList.remove('copied'); }, 2000);
        });
      }
    }
    // Timezone selector for time of day chart (data is from our own analytics, not user input)
    const rawHourCounts = {"9":11,"11":10};
    function updateHourHistogram(offsetFromPT) {
      const periods = [
        { label: "Morning (6-12)", range: [6,7,8,9,10,11] },
        { label: "Afternoon (12-18)", range: [12,13,14,15,16,17] },
        { label: "Evening (18-24)", range: [18,19,20,21,22,23] },
        { label: "Night (0-6)", range: [0,1,2,3,4,5] }
      ];
      const adjustedCounts = {};
      for (const [hour, count] of Object.entries(rawHourCounts)) {
        const newHour = (parseInt(hour) + offsetFromPT + 24) % 24;
        adjustedCounts[newHour] = (adjustedCounts[newHour] || 0) + count;
      }
      const periodCounts = periods.map(p => ({
        label: p.label,
        count: p.range.reduce((sum, h) => sum + (adjustedCounts[h] || 0), 0)
      }));
      const maxCount = Math.max(...periodCounts.map(p => p.count)) || 1;
      const container = document.getElementById('hour-histogram');
      container.textContent = '';
      periodCounts.forEach(p => {
        const row = document.createElement('div');
        row.className = 'bar-row';
        const label = document.createElement('div');
        label.className = 'bar-label';
        label.textContent = p.label;
        const track = document.createElement('div');
        track.className = 'bar-track';
        const fill = document.createElement('div');
        fill.className = 'bar-fill';
        fill.style.width = (p.count / maxCount) * 100 + '%';
        fill.style.background = '#8b5cf6';
        track.appendChild(fill);
        const value = document.createElement('div');
        value.className = 'bar-value';
        value.textContent = p.count;
        row.appendChild(label);
        row.appendChild(track);
        row.appendChild(value);
        container.appendChild(row);
      });
    }
    document.getElementById('timezone-select').addEventListener('change', function() {
      const customInput = document.getElementById('custom-offset');
      if (this.value === 'custom') {
        customInput.style.display = 'inline-block';
        customInput.focus();
      } else {
        customInput.style.display = 'none';
        updateHourHistogram(parseInt(this.value));
      }
    });
    document.getElementById('custom-offset').addEventListener('change', function() {
      const parsed = parseInt(this.value, 10);
      if (isNaN(parsed)) return;
      updateHourHistogram(parsed + 8);
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
